        "subject": "LU-459 tests: quiet spurious console/test messages",
        "message": "LU-459 tests: quiet spurious console/test messages\n\nQuiet a number of frequent and useless messages printed to the test\noutput and/or the console.  These distract from understanding what\nis happening in the test and provide little, if any, value.\n\nThe client \"acl\" mount option has been deprecated since 1.8.0, as\nit was added in mid-1.6, and is driven by the MDS config only.\n\nUse textual debug/subsystem flags instead of numeric flags.  This\nhas been possible through all of 1.8, but is deprecated in 2.x so\nwe can move to a more sophisticated debug mechanism in the future.\n\nLustre-commit: 26bb579a96efced8825b63b84465334368ecc382\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/2015\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I81bed13c22465dc179e19f5a6714b732d63ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
